"Here are the answers to the questions based on the passage:\n\n***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nThe passage describes Bond as feeling \"puny and impotent\" and being surrounded by three large men with guns. This suggests that Bond is in a vulnerable position and unlikely to escape.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n6. Very suspenseful\n\nThe passage creates a sense of tension and danger as Bond is suddenly attacked by the three men. The reader is unsure of the outcome and is left wondering how Bond will escape the situation. The use of descriptive language, such as \"the door burst in toward him\" and \"Bond felt puny and impotent\", adds to the suspenseful atmosphere."